verses:
“ माणिक्यं तरणेः सुधार्यममलं मुक्ताफलं शीतगो-
र्माद्देयस्य च विद्रुमं मरकतं सौम्यस्य गारुत्मतम् ।

"Ruby for the Sun, a pure and spotless gem; Pearl for the Moon; Coral for Mars; Emerald for Mercury;

"Those who are devoted to religious duties, devoted to twice-born gods, who eat wholesome food, and are self-controlled;
Those people who possess the limits of good family and character, to them, the learned ones have described this longevity.
Those who are greedy for sin, thieves, revilers of gods and Brahmins;
And those who eat everything, for them untimely death is certain.
Those who have wavering intellects in religion, and are haters of the wicked;
And those who steal the wealth of Brahmins and gods.
And all those who are terrible, fools, and slanderers;
And those who live by sinful deeds, devoid of the duties of their own caste.
And those who are ignorant of scriptures and deluded, they meet untimely death.
For others, the longevity mentioned above will be theirs, thus say the learned ones in scriptures." Thus.
